text.section:
In making the designation and giving approval under this section, the Board of Trustees shall consider:
the nature and extent of the rights and benefits to be provided by the annuity contracts for participating employees and their beneficiaries;
the relation of those rights and benefits to the amount of contributions to be made;
the suitability of the rights and benefits to the needs of the participating employees and the interests of the employing institutions in the recruitment and retention of participating employees;
the ability of the company to provide for suitable rights and benefits under the annuity contracts;
the selection of annuity contracts offered by the company;
the financial stability of the company and whether the company meets minimum financial criteria, if any, including a minimum net worth requirement, if any, established by the Board of Trustees; and
the effect of any fees, commissions, or other charges imposed or collected in connection with an annuity contract.
